Files.Description: Office Home and Business 2016 for Mac - DVD (Multiple Languages) – See Details
Files.Notes:
To activate your copy of Office 2016 for Mac you’ll need to visit Office.com/setup and follow the next steps:

Step 1: Obtain a Product Key from your MSDN portal, copy the product key.

Step 2: Using your Mac, go to the browser and type in the following: http://office.com/setup.

Step 3: Read the text page that appears on the screen. At the bottom of the page, there is a space for a 25-digit number. This is where the product key number should be inserted.

Step 4: Type in or paste the 25-digit number. Proofread the number to be sure it is correct.

Step 5: Click on the box that says Get Started. Create a Microsoft Account or use your existing account and begin installing Office 2016 for Mac.

Files.Description: Microsoft Dynamics CRM 2015 SDK User Interface Integration (x86) - (English)
Microsoft Dynamics CRM 2013 SDK User Interface Integration (x86) - (English)

Files.Notes:
Prior Versions
This 1.2 (build 2.0.0695.0) version resolves the following error that could occur when starting all previous versions of the WEDU client: "There was an error communicating with the server please try again later…"

Install Instructions
Remove all prior version of WEDU for Windows Embedded Standard 7 SP1 via the Control Panel before installing this version. This version will not install if you already have Windows Embedded 8 Standard Toolkit installed.

Incorrect Install Error Message
If Windows Embedded Standard 7 toolkit is not pre-installed, WEDU installer will exit and show the following error: "WEDU will exit because Windows Embedded 8 Standard is not detected on this machine." There is a typo in this error message, it should read the following: "WEDU will exit because Windows Embedded Standard 7 toolkit is not detected on this machine."
